  "prompt": "Is there a survey app which pays at least 5 dollars for easy questions?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several survey apps and platforms that offer payment for completing surveys, with some surveys paying around $5 or more for simple questions. Here are a few options you might consider:\n\n1. **Swagbucks**: This platform allows you to earn points (SB) by taking surveys, watching videos, and shopping online. You can redeem points for cash via PayPal or gift cards.\n\n2. **Survey Junkie**: This site offers a variety of surveys that can earn you points, which can be converted to cash or gift cards. Some surveys can pay around $5, depending on their length and complexity.\n\n3. **InboxDollars**: You can earn cash for taking surveys, watching videos, and other online activities. Some surveys may pay around $5.\n\n4. **YouGov**: Known for its political and social issue surveys, YouGov often rewards users with points that can be redeemed for cash or gift cards. Some surveys can be more lucrative than others.\n\n5. **Rover (formerly known as Opinion Outpost)**: This platform offers surveys that can pay quite a bit for longer or more involved questions, and occasionally you may find higher-paying quick surveys.\n\nMake sure to read user reviews and check the payment methods to determine if they align with your preferences. Additionally, pay attention to the eligibility criteria for surveys since not all participants will qualify for every survey.",
